    <h1>The web’s most popular front-end template</h1>
    <p class="description">HTML5 Boilerplate helps you build <strong>fast</strong>, <strong>robust</strong>, and <strong>adaptable</strong> web apps or sites. Kick-start your project with the combined knowledge and effort of 100s of developers, all in one little package.</p>
    <div class="cta-option">

  <div class="site-section">
   <div class="container">
    <h2>Save time. Create with confidence.</h2>
    <div class="grid">
     <div class="grid-cell">
      <h3><span class="star">?</span> Analytics, icons, and more</h3>
      <p>A lean, mobile-friendly HTML template; optimized Google Analytics snippet; placeholder touch-device icon; and docs covering dozens of extra tips and tricks.</p>
     </div>
     <div class="grid-cell">
      <h3><span class="star">?</span> Normalize.css and helpers</h3>
      <p>Includes <a href="https://necolas.github.io/normalize.css/">Normalize.css</a> — a modern, HTML5-ready alternative to CSS resets — and further base styles, helpers, media queries, and print styles.</p>
     </div>
     <div class="grid-cell">
      <h3><span class="star">?</span> jQuery and Modernizr</h3>
      <p>Get the latest minified versions of two best-of-breed libraries: <a href="https://jquery.org/">jQuery</a> (via jQuery’s CDN, with local fallback) and a custom build of the <a href="https://modernizr.com/">Modernizr</a> feature detection library.</p>
     </div>
     <div class="grid-cell">
      <h3><span class="star">?</span> High performance</h3>
      <p>Apache settings to help you deliver excellent site performance. We independently maintain <a href="https://github.com/h5bp/server-configs">server configs</a> for multiple platforms.</p>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div>
  <div class="site-section site-section-video">
   <h2>Introduction to v6</h2>
   <div class="content">
    <p class="new">What's new? Plenty. It's taken us a while to get a new version out the door, but we've been busy, so we hope you'll find it's worth the wait. Here are some highlights:</p>
    <ul class="new">
     <li>After much discussion we're now fetching jQuery from jQuery's CDN instead of Google's.</li>
     <li>After even more discussion we dropped IE8 support ?? We're now tracking to the latest Normalize and jQuery.</li>
     <li>We updated Modernizr to v3 and added a sample Modernizr configuration file so you can create your own custom build.</li>
     <li>We added a sample web app manifest file to the project to help you properly format your site or app to save to a device's home screen.</li>
     <li>That's just the tip of the iceberg. This update includes well over 100 commits from more than 45 developers. <a href="https://github.com/h5bp/html5-boilerplate/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md">Check out the Changelog for all the fun.</a></li>
    </ul>
   </div>
